    {
      "datasource": null,
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": {}, "overrides": [] },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 35 },
      "id": 7,
      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "## Grafana Setup Instructions\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Grafana 10+ with the **JSON API** plugin: `grafana-cli plugins install marcusolsson-json-datasource`\n- FastAPI running at `http://localhost:8000` (or Docker: `docker-compose up`)\n\n### 1. Add Data Source\n1. Go to **Configuration > Data Sources > Add data source**\n2. Search for **JSON API**\n3. Set **URL** to `http://localhost:8000`\n4. Click **Save & Test** — you should see \"Data source connected\"\n\n### 2. Import This Dashboard\n1. Go to **Dashboards > Import**\n2. Click **Upload dashboard JSON file** and select `grafana/dashboard.json`\n3. Map **Anomaly Detection API** to your JSON API datasource\n4. Click **Import**\n\n### 3. Populate History (run at least once)\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/simulate \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"sensor_id\":\"PUMP_01\",\"anomaly_type\":\"bearing_wear\",\"severity\":0.85,\"language\":\"both\"}'\n```\n\n### API Quick Reference\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| GET | /health | System health check |\n| POST | /simulate | Inject synthetic anomaly + RCA |\n| POST | /analyze | Full detection + RCA pipeline |\n| GET | /history | Last 10 analyses (newest first) |",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Setup & Import Guide",
      "type": "text"
    }
